The King found at Southvvell, and the Oxford gigg playd, and sung at VVitney VVakes: vvith the masque shevved before divers courtiers, and cavaliers, that went thither from Oxford, and severall ketches and songs at the said vvakes. Presented to the Duke of Yorke. / By Mr. Loyd, studient of Christ Church in Oxford, and a captaine of that garison. Lloyd, M., Captain.
8 p.
printed for F.L., London : 1646.
Annotation on Thomason copy: "May 7th". Reproduction of the original in the British Library.
